        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/29/4" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2009.29.issue-4/asset/14a168ae-a214-168a-4a21-a168ae4a214a/radiographics.2009.29.issue-4.cover.gif" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">4</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jul 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1003</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1026</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19605653/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19605653</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jul 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.294085748">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=CBD+%3D+common+bile+duct&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">CBD = common bile duct</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=ERCP+%3D+endoscopic+retrograde+cholangiopancreatography&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">ERCP = endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MPD+%3D+main+pancreatic+duct&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MPD = main pancreatic duct</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The clinical and radiologic features of various uncommon types of acute and chronic pancreatitis, congenital pancreatic anomalies associated with pancreatitis, and some unusual causes of pancreatitis are discussed and illustrated.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Alampady Krishna Prasad</span> <span property="familyName">Shanbhogue</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Texas HSC at San Antonio, 7703 Floyd Curl Dr, San Antonio, TX 78229 (A.K.P.S.); Department of Diagnostic Imaging, Ottawa Hospital, Civic Campus, Ottawa, Ontario, Canada (N.F., G.P.D., D.K.P.S.); Department of Radiology, University of Texas HSC at Houston, Tex (V.R.S.); and Department of Radiology, VIMHANS Hospital, New Delhi, India (S.K.S.). Received September 25, 2008; revision requested December 11; final revision received February 20, 2009; accepted March 4. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Shanbhogue/Alampady+Krishna+Prasad" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Najla</span> <span property="familyName">Fasih</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">FRCR</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Texas HSC at San Antonio, 7703 Floyd Curl Dr, San Antonio, TX 78229 (A.K.P.S.); Department of Diagnost